 Q1. The numbers appear to be close to but not exactly following a pattern of even numbers, with a range of 124 to 182. The difference between consecutive numbers varies, and there doesn't seem to be a consistent pattern in the differences.

Q2. The numbers in this set are mostly prime numbers, with the exceptions being 101, 103, and 137. A prime number is a natural number greater than 1 that has no positive divisors other than 1 and itself. The range of these prime numbers is 101 to 199, and they are not in any particular order. [end of text]


